		<img width="2500" height="1200" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter.jpg" class="singlepostthumb wp-post-image" alt="" decoding="async" fetchpriority="high" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter.jpg 2500w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter-520x250.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter-1200x576.jpg 1200w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter-768x369.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter-1536x737.jpg 1536w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter-2048x983.jpg 2048w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/header-brave-little-hunter-900x432.jpg 900w" sizes="(max-width: 2500px) 100vw, 2500px" /><div class="post-thumbnail-caption">Government workers and local volunteers spent more than a month trying to coax kʷiisaḥiʔis (Brave Little Hunter), a juvenile killer whale, out of a British Columbia tidal lagoon. The rescue effort cost more than CAN $250,000. Photo by THE CANADIAN PRESS/Chad Hipolito</div>
			<article class="main container col4">
								<header class="maincol">
										<h1 class="pagetitle">Life, Death, and Dollars Spent</h1>
										<h2 class="dek singlepagecontainer">The Canadian government and the Ehattesaht First Nation dropped a huge chunk of change trying to save the stranded killer whale kʷiisaḥiʔis (Brave Little Hunter). Now, they’re wondering how to make up the money.</h2>
										<section class="singlebyline singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Authored by</h3>
						by  
										<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/larry-pynn/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_top" >Larry Pynn</a>								<br/>
												</section>
					 
					<aside class="singlebydatewords singlepagecontainer">
						<h3 class="invis">Wordcount</h3>
						August 22, 2024 | 1,300 words, about 6 minutes
					</aside>

					
				</header>

				
